ation. --> performed by Ray LaMontagne and The Pariah Dogs<!-- No redundant link as there is no separate article for The Pariah Dogs, who are merely LaMontagne\'s backing band per the \\"Beg, Steal or Borrow\\" article. -->\\n*Brody Brown, [[Cee Lo Green]], [[The Smeezingtons|Ari Levine]], [[The Smeezingtons|Philip Lawrence]] & [[Bruno Mars]]<!-- Levine & Lawrence don\'t have their own separate articles, so they\'re linked to The Smeezingtons article.  Mars has his own article, so he links there even though he\'s also one of The Smeezingtons. --> for \\"[[Fuck You (Cee Lo Green song)|F*** You]]\\"<!-- Though censorship of expletives normally isn\'t found in Wikipedia, the song\'s Grammy nominations were all officially censored in the exact manner used here. --> performed by Cee Lo Green \\n*[[Tom Douglas]] & [[Allen Shamblin]] for \\"[[The House That Built Me]]\\" performed by [[Miranda Lambert]]\\n*[[Alex da Kid|Alexander Grant]], [[Skylar Grey]]<!-- *DO NOT* change to her real name; both her nomination and her Wikipedia article are under her stage name. --> & [[Eminem|Marshall Mathers]]<!-- Whenever the real name of a rapper is used in a Wikipedia article, for informational purposes (i.e., moving mouse pointer over link) the link should *ALWAYS* use the *actual* title of his\\/her Wikipedia article, which is almost always his\\/her stage name (the only notable exception is Tupac Shakur). *DO NOT* put *just* \\"Marshall Mathers\\" in link, even though it redirects to Eminem. --> for \\"[[Love the Way You Lie]]\\" performed by [[Eminem]]<!-- As with Maxwell the year before, redundant link is kept just in case. --> featuring [[Rihanna]]\\n| style=\\"text-align:center;\\"|<ref name=Grammy2011>{{cite web|url=http:\\/\\/www.grammy.com\\/nominees?year=2010&genre=13|title=53rd Annual GRAMMY Awards Nominees And Winners: General Field|publisher=[[Recording Academy|The Recording Academy]]|accesdate=December 10, 2011}}<\\/ref>\\n|-\\n! scope=\\"row\\"|[[54th Grammy Awards|201